The paper proposes a novel model for multi-scenario ranking using multi-agent reinforcement learning. The model involves communication between agents, private actors for making actions, and a centralized critic for evaluating overall performance. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
